ZooKeeper is a distributed coordination system used to manage:
  configuration
  leader election
  distributed locks
  service discovery
  metadata coordination

Quorum requirement
ZooKeeper uses quorum-based replication
Requires majority (N/2 + 1) nodes to operate
Example:
3 nodes → quorum = 2
5 nodes → quorum = 3
👉 This ensures fault tolerance

Throughput pattern
  read-heavy workloads perform best
  write-heavy workloads degrade quickly due to quorum sync

Znode size limit
  recommended: < 1 MB per znode
  ZooKeeper is NOT for large data storage
